<paragraph blockId="17.[113,765,175,785]" pageId="17" pageNumber="65">
Culture characteristics — Colony on PDA showing optimal growth at 25 ° 
<collectionCode box="[258,276,527,550]" country="Denmark" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/na0h-6vfh" name="University of Copenhagen" pageId="17" pageNumber="65" type="Herbarium">
<collectionCodeEnum box="[258,276,527,550]" pageId="17" pageNumber="65">C</collectionCodeEnum>
</collectionCode>
with an average growth rate of 
<quantity box="[603,737,527,550]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="17" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="2.2" valueMin="1.3">1.3–2.2 mm</quantity>
/d. Colony reverse, rosy buff becoming white towards the margins, turning cinnamon to fawn with age and pigmented. Colony surface cottony, rosy buff becoming white towards the margin, turning hazel with age. Aerial mycelium abundant, cottony, with high sporulation and lacking exudates.
</paragraph>
