<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="65" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[113,763,807,1006]" pageId="17" pageNumber="65">
Notes — 
<taxonomicName box="[244,536,807,830]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Nectriaceae" genus="Fusarium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="17" pageNumber="65" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="tanahbumbuense">
<emphasis box="[244,536,807,830]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="65">Fusarium tanahbumbuense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from the fungus illustrated as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berkeley &amp; Ravenel" authorityYear="1875" box="[428,576,837,860]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Nectriaceae" genus="Fusarium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="17" pageNumber="65" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="semitectum">
<emphasis box="[428,576,837,860]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="65">
<collectionCodeEnum box="[428,443,837,860]" pageId="17" pageNumber="65">F</collectionCodeEnum>
. semitectum
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Leslie &amp; Sum- merell (2006) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Nelson PE &amp; Toussoun TA &amp; Marasas WFO" box="[302,504,866,889]" journalOrPublisher="Pennsylvania State University Press, US" pageId="17" pageNumber="65" refId="ref16816" refString="Nelson PE, Toussoun TA, Marasas WFO. 1983. Fusarium species: An illus- trated manual for identification. Pennsylvania State University Press, US." title="Fusarium species: An illus- trated manual for identification" type="book" year="1983">Nelson et al. (1983)</bibRefCitation>
by the absence of microconidia and chlamydospores. The polyphialides observed for this species also greatly differed from those that have been observed for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berkeley &amp; Ravenel" authorityYear="1875" box="[251,398,954,977]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Nectriaceae" genus="Fusarium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="17" pageNumber="65" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="semitectum">
<emphasis box="[251,398,954,977]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="65">
<collectionCodeEnum box="[251,266,954,977]" pageId="17" pageNumber="65">F</collectionCodeEnum>
. semitectum
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which have 3–5 openings (
<bibRefCitation author="Nelson PE &amp; Toussoun TA &amp; Marasas WFO" journalOrPublisher="Pennsylvania State University Press, US" pageId="17" pageNumber="65" refId="ref16816" refString="Nelson PE, Toussoun TA, Marasas WFO. 1983. Fusarium species: An illus- trated manual for identification. Pennsylvania State University Press, US." title="Fusarium species: An illus- trated manual for identification" type="book" year="1983">Nelson et al. 1983</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
